  "name": "John 16:1–15",
  "localizedName": "John 16:1–15",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus warned the disciples that they would be "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108054",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "treated badly"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " after he was gone."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "This made the disciples very sad."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "But Jesus promised that when he left the Holy Spirit would come. He would be a wonderful gift for Jesus’ followers."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Spirit would show that Jesus was telling the truth about the Father. The Holy Spirit would also show people their sin."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He would help them see that they weren’t living how Jesus taught them to live. He would also show them that the devil didn’t have power over them anymore."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He would be with Jesus’ followers as a true friend. Through the Holy Spirit Jesus’ followers would stay joined to Jesus and the Father."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
